data.value:
It is highly recommended to start with the Sardaukar Campaign as the story is, chronologically, starting one day after the ending of War of Assassins: Sandstorm.
The Atreides, Harkonnen and Ordos campaigns take place after the end of the Sardaukar campaign, and their order doesn't matter. Each campaign offers the perspective of that particular House over the war, and some of the story elements might find their explanations in another House's campaign.
After selecting a mission, you can view some intel information about certain characters involved in the story, military equipment or history of a specific House. It is advised to read them to have a better understanding of the story.
A tactical map is also available for some missions, which will show that mission's tactical position of troops and attack paths for the planet they are on.

data.name: IntroOutroRichTextBox.Text
data.value:
Created by Feda
If you didn't play the War of Assassins and Sandstorm campaigns, it is highly recommended you do so. This is a sequel to War of Assassins: Sandstorm. The lore and characters stay mostly true to the books and the Dune universe, but some things have been changed, so this is a slightly altered lore.
The deadly War of Assassins that emperor Shaddam IV created and, later, joined, has killed millions. His plans will now never be revealed, as emperor Shaddam IV is most likely dead, inside the ruins of his destroyed Palace in the Imperial Basin. Without an emperor, the Sardaukar armies on Arrakis are in disarray. Many bursegs have decided to stop fighting the Landsraad coalition of the Atreides, Harkonnen and Ordos, and focus on finding a way to return to Kaitain, to ensure the protection of the Corrino heir, princess Irulan Corrino. Others decided to stand and fight until the very last moment, while others are blaming the Guild for Shaddam's death.
While it may seem that, with Shaddam presumably dead, the war will end, that is far from being true. The three Great Houses are still hunting down any Sardaukar or Guild forces, outraged for their interference in the war. But this is the Atreides, Harkonnen and Ordos we're talking about: such an alliance cannot last for long, and when it breaks, it shall be war again. However, this time, without an emperor to ensure order within the Imperium, other Landsraad Houses are tempted to get involved too, to profit from the instability and get some certain advantages. While Irulan is the rightful heir, most members of the Landsraad do not wish for a female heir, and even a young one. The Imperium has to choose a male emperor, according to the old laws, but that was not always respected. However, for a female heir to be crowned, the Landsraad must vote and agree on this.
With all the instability that comes after the First Spice War, which technically ended with the death of emperor Shaddam IV, you must be ready to lead the Sardaukar and the three Great Houses through these difficult and uncertain times. Good luck, commander.
